# OMR Engine — dev environment overrides
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (which is gitignored) and fill in your values.
# Vite injects any variable prefixed `VITE_` into the client bundle at build time.
#
# ── Dev auto-login ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When set, AuthGate skips the magic-link flow and signs the user in directly.
# Active in `vite` dev mode only (import.meta.env.DEV). Production builds ignore
# these variables entirely — the magic-link flow remains the only path in prod.
#
# Rotate VITE_DEV_USER_TOKEN whenever the underlying D1 emailVerificationToken
# rotates. Token is the same value `omr-worker` validates as X-API-Token.

VITE_DEV_USER_EMAIL=
VITE_DEV_USER_TOKEN=
VITE_DEV_USER_ROLE=
